OL,3,CTanni Grey-Thompson 'not surprised' by
OL,4,Cdamning disabled transport report
OL,6,F"It needs to happen always in the same
OL,7,Fway that health and safety and such
OL,8,Flike should happen always. What we
OL,9,Fneed is guaranteed and enforceable and
OL,10,Fenforced access to transport. Sadly at
OL,11,Fthe moment that's not what we've got."
OL,13,FHe said that in a world where the
OL,14,Fnumber of human employees always seems
OL,15,Fto be shrinking, "accessibility is
OL,16,Falways the afterthought".
OL,18,FDisability rights campaigner Adam
OL,19,FGabsi, who lives in London, said he
OL,20,F"tends not to think too much otherwise
OL,21,Fconcerns can consume you".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
